---
import "../../styles/global.css";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <title>CNN Detection - Xi Lin</title>
  </head>
  <body class="bg-white text-gray-900">
    <main class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-16 sm:px-10">
      <a href="/" class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-500 hover:text-gray-900">Back to home</a>
      <p class="mt-6 text-sm font-mono text-blue-600">IEEE IPIC 2023 | First Author</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">Research on Object Detection of Robotic Based on Convolutional Neural Network</h1>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-4xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
        This earlier undergraduate publication focused on CNN-based robotic object detection and practical visual-navigation integration. The work included YOLOv5 deployment and optimization, VOC2012 evaluation, and migration of a VINS-Fusion-based pipeline toward UAV-style navigation scenarios.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-10 overflow-hidden rounded-[28px] border border-gray-200 bg-white">
        <img src="/assets/projects/undergrad-trajectory.png" alt="CNN detection plot" class="w-full object-contain" />
      </div>

      <section class="mt-10 rounded-[28px] border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-6 sm:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Project Note</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
          I keep this publication here mainly as an early record of my undergraduate exploration in perception and robotics. The visible plot is more useful than the paper text itself for this homepage, so I only include the figure and the high-level summary here.
        </p>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
